    <b>Event: 2015 NorCal Special Elders and Responsible Ones Training</b>
    <div class="application_section">
    <b><u>Training Media:</u></b><br/>
    The training audio files from last Saturday (1/17) are now available <b><a href="media.html"/>HERE</b>.<br/><br/>
    <b><u>Consecration Agreement:</u></b><br/>
    Click <a href="consecration.html"/><b>HERE</b></a> to read and sign.<br/><br/>
    </div>
    <div class="application_section">
    <b><u>Registration Fee:</u></b><br/>
    $150.00<br/><br/>
    <b><u>Training Dates:</u></b><br/>
    Jan 17, Feb 14, Mar 21, Apr 18, May 16, Jun 20<br/>
    <i>(Third saturday of every month <b>except</b> February)</i><br/><br/>
    <b><u>Training Location:</u></b><br/>
    Jan - Mar: South San Francisco Conference Center<br/>
    Apr - Jun: TBD<br/><br/>
    <b><u>Time:</u></b><br/>
    9 am to 1 pm<br/><br/>
    <b><u>Practical Aspects:</u></b>
    <ul style="margin-top: 0;">
	<li>The training is one year in length.</li>
        <li>During the 4-hour session on each Saturday morning, there will be 3 lessons. Total of 36 lessons in one year.</li>
	<li>Lesson materials are given out on the day of the training session to the registered brothers.</li>
	<li>Do not copy the lesson materials. Do not share the materials with anyone outside of your locality.</li>
	<li>Meetings will be recorded and will be accessible with a password.</li>
	<li>Try to arrange your shcedule so as to not miss any meeting.</li>
	   	<ul>
		<li>Saturday meetings - 3 excused absences are allowed and you are to make up by listening to the recordings. No unexcused absences are allowed.</li>
		<li>Weekly local sessions - 1 to 1.5 hours; require a 75% attendance</li>
		</ul>
	<li>First training session is January 17, 2015</li>
    </ul>
    <b><u>Application Procedure</u></b>
    <ol style="margin-top: 0;" type="1">
	<li>Submit the following application form, and you will also need a recommendation from the leading brothers in your locality.</li>
	<li>Sign a consecration agreement, which is a commitment to make all the meetings and do all the assignments. (The consecration agreement will be sent out later)</li>
    </ol>
    <b><u>Payment Procedure</u></b>
    <ul style="margin-top: 0;">
     	<li> Choose the online payment option in the registration form if possible.</li>
	<li> There is no need to have a PayPal account to use the online payment.</li>
	<li> If you choose to pay by check, give the check to the responsible brother in your locality.</li>
	<li> Each locality should bring one check payable to "Church in San Jose" on the first day of training.</li>
    </ul>
    <b><u>Application Deadline</u></b><br/>
    January 1st, 2015<br/><br/>
    <b><u>Note</u></b><br/> Registration for the training is closed. <br/>Email admin@churchincambridge.org if you need any help.<br/><br/>

